	All right but there are better in vegas	We had reserved a King non smoking room with strip view, but when we arrived all they had left were king smoking or two queen beds non smoking. We took the two queens. The room is very modern, the TV is a large flat screen, and the beds (even if they were queens) were extremely comfortable. One great thing is that there was a fairly large safe in the room. The pool area is large and beautiful (unfortunately the temp was only in the high 50's F when we were there so we did not get to use the pool) .The cleaning staff did a great job. The room was spotless. We never saw them but they always came and did a wonderful job.When playing with the TV I noticed you could check your hotel bill. When I did I saw a charge for $30 for taking items from the fridge. Since we had not even opened the fridge I complained and they took the amount off my bill. So make sure you look at your bill.One of the only negatives about the room is that the door was not very soundproof. We could hear everything going on in the hallways. Another issue is that though the rooms have wi fi, there is a $15 charge for 24 hours use.Perhaps the biggest negative about the hotel itself is the casino. It is getting old. There is a distinct smell of smoke that you do not get at the other hotels, and the feel is darker and less appealing. We ate at the Buffet for breakfast. It is rather plain, which is not acceptable for the price you pay. We also ate at their steak restaurant named Stacks. It is expensive but I had the best steak I have ever eaten. You could cut it with a fork. Highly recommended. As for entertainment, if you have the chance see the Beatles Love. It is a fantastic experience. The performance is less acrobatics and more dance than is normal for Cirque. The dancing and Beatles music is just magic.To sum up there is nothing terribly wrong with the MIrage but next time I think we will try another Hotel.	
