Nov 24 2009 	Good experience at the Mirage	We are frequent visitors to Vegas and decided to try the Mirage this time around. The location is ideal for visiting many of the other major hotels and it's close to the &quot;middle&quot; of the strip. The free tram to Treasure Island is also a plus. Check-in was quick and efficient, and the overall service of the staff was excellent. We had no difficulty getting a non-smoking room and we were pleased with the newly renovated room. The main area was large, but the bathroom was small for Vegas standards. The shower/tub combination was roomy with a curved shower curtain bar, but the showerhead was a bit dated. The modern touches in the room were nice, but I got the overall impression that cheaper materials were used in construction compared to other Vegas hotels we've visited. The bed was very comfortable and the flatscreen TV was nice, including a few HD channels.The soundproofing in the rooms wasn't the best, and we could hear quite a bit of activity in the hallways. Maid service was good overall, but without any special touches.We liked the fact that the casino was smaller than others and manageable as far as getting around and staying oriented. As far as food, we had the buffet (Cravings) for breakfast a couple of days, which was average, and the Carnegie Deli was good for huge sandwiches, and they have a take-out window.The Mirage is a good option for anyone staying in Vegas. As an aside, you are able to rent a mobility scooter at the hotel if you have special needs.	
