Nov 22 2009 	Good Location Nice Rooms	We planned to make a trip to Vegas around Halloween and were searching for a decent room at a good price. After some searching we decided to stay at the Mirage at about $90/nt including the weekend.The casino was quite busy when we arrived. We arrived at about 1:00 PM and were happy to see that are rooms were ready. We needed two rooms, but couldn't get connecting rooms, but they managed to have only one room between us. It was a bit of a trek from the front desk to the elevators, but we got used to it by end of the trip.The rooms were quite nice, the decor was quite modern and you can definitely see that they renovated the rooms. The beds were quite comfortable and there was plenty of drawer space for our clothes. We checked the TV and were surprised for once that the HDTV's actually had HD channels. We didn't watch much TV, but none the less that was a nice surprise when you consider other hotels don't have any HD Channels. The washrooms are about average size. There is only one sink and their is adequate room on both sides for all the toiletries that we brought. The soaps and shampoos provided were from Gilcrest &amp; Soames. They had a nice scent and they were replaced daily.There was also a room safe and a bar fridge in the room. The safe will fit a laptop if you have one, but you will have to put it on it's side, so be careful when you open it. The bar fridge was quite stocked up with the usual drinks and foods (all priced above normal) along with some other products including cosmetics, shaving needs and even condoms.The staff was friendly whenever we encountered them and our rooms were always clean when we came back to the room. If you have the opportunity, you should definitely try to catch LOVE. We managed to get our tickets at 50% off for the promotion that they had that weekend and caught the show on Halloween. It was one of the best shows we have seen in Vegas in quite some time.Location wise, it was perfect and it was a nice hub to walk between all the other casinos and shops on the Strip. It was hopping on the strip on Halloween and the costumes were quite plentiful (myself included). I was the Oriental Elvis, if you happened to spot me.The slots at the Casino weren't great at the beginning of our stay, but the last day there I managed to recoup almost all of my losses. It was nice to leave with more than $20 in my pocket at the end of my stay.We had only one meal at the Casino and it was the final morning at the Buffet. It was a little better than most of the breakfast buffets we've had in the past. The price of food in general at most restaurants appeared to ride on the high side of medium, but it didn't appear to be super expensive.Overall, we quite enjoyed our stay and are definitely considering coming back. We didn't want to feel that we were entitled like some other people and I feel that if you treat the staff with a smile and are polite, they will always reciprocate. It worked and we felt quite welcome.	
