Nov 15 2009 	Outstanding	My wife and I stayed at the Mirage from Oct. 31 to Nov. 2. It was my second stay there this year. In both cases, the rooms were complimentary, but I would pay regular rate to come again. The rooms have been recently renovated, and are excellent. Good sized, nicely furnished, great bed, flat-screen TV. Both the rooms and the common areas were very clean and well-maintained. The bathrooms were nicely renovated. My only complaint - a minor one - is that the bathrooms are relatively small, with only a standard tub/shower combination. Most of the newer hotels, of course, have larger bathrooms with separate tubs and showers. Overall, however, I would give the rooms an excellent rating. The casino is very comfortable, with a good selection of games and gaming limits. Five dollar table games were available during most times of the day, which was a plus for us since we are not high-rollers. The availability of low-limit table games kept us on site when we would otherwise have gone in search of cheaper play elsewhere. The location is very good, with tram access to Treasure Island, and a short walk to the Wynn, other casinos and the mall.Good selection of restaurants on site, including a California Pizza Kitchen, a deli and a burger restaurant. Starbucks as well. But if you're not a total coffee snob, there is a second coffee shop in the retail pavillion (on the way to the pool). The lines are not nearly as long first thing in the a.m. and the selection of muffins and rolls is better than the Starbucks. The service was a bit disappointing. We needed to pick up tickets to Jay Leno and were told at the front desk to go to the Concierge. The Concierge said they did not handle tickets and told us to go to the Terry Fator box office after 3:30, which we did. No one was there, so we asked at the business center. We were told to come back at 4:00, which we did. Still no one there. We called the front desk and were told they did not open until 4:30. After explaining the run-around we had gotten, the front desk told us to go to the other box office (Beatles &quot;Love&quot;). The front desk said to go directly to the side of the ticket counter (ahead of everyone standing in line). The desk said they would call ahead and let them know we were coming. We did as we were told - suffering numerous dirty looks from the folks standing in line - but the ticket counter had not been called. Nevertheless, they were very accommodating and issued our tickets on the spot. Service in the casino was also spotty. Difficult to find wait staff on the casino floor to order drinks. But I have found that to be the case at every casino I've visited this year.All in all, an excellent property and one that I will definitely visit again. I highly recommend it.	
