Nov 7 2009 	All things good	Our first trip to vegas and arrived at the mirage at 4pm and found myself struggling to open a heavy door with a suitcase and found it rather strange to not have an automatic door. Then proceeded to a very quick check in. Was not offered a free upgrade, although was offered a penthouse for $60 a night which we declined. We then walked the long walk to the elevators right through the casino, which I guess is standard with every hotel in vegas to do this. Was given a very nice king deluxe room overlooking part of the strip and the pool. The room was very spacious and the bed was amazing. Yes the bathroom could of been bigger but was very modern and clean. House keeping could not be faulted. We ate in Cravings buffet a few mornings and were happy with the choices although felt we had to keep asking the waitress for tea, orange juice etc. Beware that the price goes up about $10 at the weekend. We also ate in california pizza kitchen which was lovely and the BLT burger which was just ok and nothing special for the price. Not to be missed is the Love, Cirque de soleil, which was amazing and worth every penny and would pay again and again to see it.We generally went to the pool around 3pm and had no problem at all getting seats and was generally quiet. was nice to sit at the Dolphin bar beside the pool, but beware of the very high price of the drinks here.Visited most of the hotels on the strip and would recommend visiting the ferrari collection at the wynn, Watching the Bellagio fountains from the Eiffel Tower at night and the volcano at The mirage. The monrail system is a godsend and runs very late although again a bit pricey.We were very happy with The Mirage on the whole, the location is excellent, how ever i think some of the other hotels like MGM and New York New york offer better facilities, although we cannot comment on the rooms there.	
