Oct 29 2009 	Modern decor great buffet clean rooms and great location on the strip	This was our 2nd trip to Vegas (we stayed at the Bellagio the first time). We came to see a Pepper concert and the Grand Canyon, which I highly recommend if you have a whole day to kill.This hotel was great. The room is very modern looking and the bed was comfortable. We had a strip view room, so we had a view of the erupting volcano each night which was cool. The pool is huge, with a nice waterfall. You need to get there early though, if you want a lounge chair (there were none available for us). We were only in the pool for about 1/2 hour when they made everyone get out due to a chlorine explosion, which was disappointing since it was our only day to enjoy the pool. We ate at the buffet a lot, which is enormous and more cost effective than the other restaurants in the hotel. We tried the burger place and were not impressed. Also, if you walk across the street there is a Dennys which we found for breakfast, with the same prices as the one back home. Next to Dennys there is also a food court with some inexpensive food. The location of this hotel is great, righ in the middle of the strip. Overall I thought the hotel was great and would definitely stay there again. The only thing it lacked was a jacuzzi tub, which I guess you have to pay more for, but we have gotten them with standard rooms before. You really can't go wrong with this hotel.	
Oct 29 2009 	Great location good service newly renovated rooms	The whole family (including grandparents and a toddler) stayed at Mirage for 3 nights in October. We arrived on Saturday noon and the lobby was not crowed. The lady at the front desk spent at lease 10 minutes to find two rooms next to each other for us, which was very much appreciated. She also ordered a crib and a refrigerator for us as requested. Both the crib and refrigerator were free. The hotel is old; however, the rooms are newly renovated. The decoration is contemporary, with a big flat screen TV on the wall. Size of the rooms as well as the bath rooms are kind of small, normal size for a regular hotel, though. Our rooms got a pool view (paid extra for that) and part of the Strip view, which was very pretty. The rooms were very quiet, too. The location of the hotel is just AWESOME. With the help of a stroller, we managed to visit almost all well-known casinos from Wynn to Mandalay Bay (we did call Taxi for a few times to catch the shows and the cost was only $7-10 bucks each way). We didn't swim but did walk around the swimming pool area. It was nice. It was in the 60s so not lots of people were in the pool area. We were disappointed with Dolphin Habitat, though. There was no dolphin show, no nothing, just several dolphins swimming around. They don't even have a scheduled feeding time. So if you need to pay $15 to get in, please save your money for something else. We booked the rooms via Mirage's web site. Through their 25th anniversary package, we got free tickets to the Dolphin Habitat and $40 credit per room toward the Carving Buffett. Saturday night stay was the most expensive one, and Monday night was the cheapest. The average price we paid for the three nights was about $138 per night per room plus tax. The price included the premium to upgrade the view. So overall I think it was a reasonable deal. We are not gamblers, and we were with a toddler, so we didn't spend lots of time in the Casino. No comments on that. Overall I like this hotel, especially the location. I'll recommend to my friends but I myself will try some other hotels next time.	
Oct 28 2009 	Great Stay in Las Vegas	We were planning on staying in Las Vegas for 2 nights, and wanted something right on the strip, allowing us to walk to all of our destinations. The Mirage has a perfect location. We parked in the self-park garage (free), checked in very quickly and walked to our room. The walk from the self-park garage to our room was quite a trek, but all of the strip hotels have you walk through the casino to reach the guest elevators. The room, on the 17th floor, was lovely; large and very comfortable. Great bed, pillows and shower. I loved the huge magnifying mirror in the bathroom. I wish that every hotel had one! Great view from the windows. We ate breakfast at the Denny's across the street, which was much more reasonable than the Mirage restaurants, for breakfast. We did eat lunch at the Carnegie Deli, at the Mirage, and it was very good and huge!! We took the advice of another Trip Advisor review and signed the Mirage Guest Book prior to booking our room. As a result, we received a very good email offer for a low room rate, which I booked. Bottom line, a great stay!	
Oct 28 2009 	Wonderful	We checked in early in the afternoon, and although the type of room we specified wasn't ready they assigned us a room that was about equal and was ready. And, without me asking, they announced the rate was lower. So we saved a few dollars, and still ended up with a great upper-story room that was quiet and had a fabulous view of the volcano and the strip. We paid about $220 including all the lugs. The room had obviously been remodeled in the last couple years, it was well appointed, with an excellent TV and bathroom. It would have benefited by the addition of an easy chair. The hotel was crowded, and the lines at the restaurants and the packed swimming pool area were problems. Plus, the restaurant service was slow. But the food was good and we really enjoyed our stay.	
Oct 28 2009 	Not a Mirage	We visited the Mirage in September for our anniversary. We arrived at about 4:00 and unfortunately our room wasn't ready yet, so we just had a drink at the bar while we waited. About an hour later our room was ready. We were given exactly what we reserved. A king room on the 12th floor overlooking the volcano. My only complaint was, even though we requested a smoking room, the room continually smelled of smoke. It seems that is day and age there has to be a way to get that smell out. Other than that, the room was great. As many have said, the bathroom is quite small, but you eventually get used to it. I love the fact that the window opened. It balanced out the air conditioner and also allowed fresh air to circulate into the room. On our first night the hotel sent up a bottle of champagne for our anniversary. I thought was a great touch. The couple of times we ordered room service, it was delivered promptly and the food was good for the price. The staff was great. The location can't be beat. It's right in the middle of the strip, so everything is just a few minutes away. Overall the Mirage is a great hotel with great staff. We will definately consider a stay in the future.	
