Oct 24 2009 	This first timer is HAPPY!!	Stayed for 4 nights, 3 full days. Check-in and out were both quick and easy. Booked a king bed with a pool view, but got double beds in the room. Was immediately ,without drama, upgraded to a newly renovated king room on the very top floor with lotsa room and a gorgeous spa bathroom (double vanites, seperate glass shower, jetted tub, tile floor to ceiling). Room service was tasty but expensive. Casino wasn't overly smoky. Food was average at the BLT. Guest service was excellent. Large area to walk, but nice nonetheless. Good location to the nicer resorts and free shows. Definitely well kept and the pool was dreamy (large with a bridge and a grotto with waterfalls). Get a good rate and check it out!	
Oct 23 2009 	Great location mid-Strip; "Brand new" following complete renovation	We stayed at the Mirage for three nights. After exploring several options on the Strip, we found a great rate at the Mirage and knew that they had recently remodeled. We arrived at the hotel mid-morning after an early morning flight. Like most Strip hotels, the place is bustling -- even on a Sunday morning. Lots of traffic, lots of people out front, in the lobby, heading to and from the casino, etc. We didn't expect our rooms to be ready, but were pleasantly surprised to discover they were. The front desk staff was very friendly and check-in was very speedy.Also like most Strip hotels, it's a long walk from the front desk to the elevators -- and you have to go through the casino to get there. Though I don't remember specifics about what the place looked like prior to the remodel, the renovations were evident. The public areas of the hotel had a very &quot;current&quot; look and feel, without being too trendy. When we arrived at our rooms -- WOW!!! It was, for all purposes, a completely new hotel. This not a case of simply painting over old wallpaper. Every surface, every fixture, every thing in our room was brand new! The room was very spacious -- as is the case in most Strip hotels. The beds were very comfortable. The bathroom was huge. The new flat screen TV was awesome. For those who do have to work while in Vegas, there was a large, functional desk area with a comfortable chair. The style of the room (fabrics, colors, design, etc.) was definitely bold -- but not garish. Very hip and modern without being tacky.The employees we did encounter at the hotel were friendly. But don't expect a lot of personal attention. The Mirage is a typical, very large, and always busy Vegas resort. It's a very fun property and the room is very clean and comfortable, but the sheer volume of guests and their constant turnover prohibits very much personal service. The location of the Mirage is awesome -- great mid-Strip location, right across from the Venetian and its shopping, right next door the Forum Shops and Caesar's Palace, and a short walk from the Bellagio and its fountains.All in all, its a practically brand new hotel following their very extensive remodeling. Definitely a great value, given its prime location on the Las Vegas Strip.	
