Oct 20 2009 	Another excellent stay at the Mirage	We arrived at the Mirage and were upgraded to a Tower Deluxe room on 25th Floor. The room was beautiful, big screen TV and beautiful bathroom. The room was spotless although the refurbishment was starting to show signs of wear. The TV had a big scratch on the front panel but other than that it was a good standard. Contrary to other reports there was little noise of doors slamming and housekeeping starting knocking on doors from about 930am. You can always put the &quot;privacy please&quot; sign on your door to be sure you are not to be disturbed.The food and beverage outlets were expensive for what they offered, consequently we did not use them much, as the strip has lots of choices,many with keener prices.The casino was busy and the atmosphere was great. I asked for some comp tickets to the Secret Garden but was told I would need to charge everything to the room and play a lot in the casino and then come back and they would see what they could do. I decided against playing there very much as I was not satisfied with this. .On previous visits having done exactly that, I got no ofters from the Players Club for anything and I expected better. Their loss. This time, I enrolled at several other casinos and I will wait to see if I get some enticing offers. The one cents slot machines paid out the best, only many occasions I turned $5 into to over $100 - Forget the tighter Wheel Of Fortune machines, they just don't seem to pay out much these days!The pool continues to be fabulous but it does get very rowdy at weekends when the place becomes overrun with drunken 20 somethings standing in the pool constantly drinking. Mid week is the best time to come here as it is more relaxing and sophisticated.Tips: Don't bother prebooking shows as most of them are discounted and you can get tickets at the last minute theatre ticket agencies, even top line acts Bette Midler and Cirque Du Soleil. I got tickets for Ka at the MGM Grand for $75.00 - the face value was $113.00 and the seats were good.Beware of pickpockets, I was scammed downtown when I gave a few quarters to a supposedly needy person and had someone grab some cash from my pocket. I also lost money at the pool side, so keep an eye on your belongings!Going from the airport our cab driver tried the &quot;Freeway is much quicker routine&quot; but we opted for the backstreets and it cost $25 including a tip, so don't listen to their &quot;friendly&quot; advice.The shops are really suffering in Las Vegas. Check out Macys in the Fashion Show Mall, their prices were the same as the outlets and it is easier to get to.The Mirage continues to be a good choice because of the location and the pool. There are swankier places and the hotel is not cheap. Next year when City Centre opens with several new hotels, this might have to change as the competition is only going to increase. I will have to think long and hard about returning as the competition nearby looks extremely appealing, especially Palazzo, Wynn, Encore &amp; Mandalay Bay.Hopefully, the Mirage will send some good offers my way this time!	
