Oct 17 2009 	Exceeded expectations	I found a very cheap trip to the Mirage and was expecting it to be decent but nothing spectacular. I was wrong though, the room was beautiful with a nice view of the strip. It was very modern yet comfortable, and felt like home for the time I was there. The bed was great, I can see why they sell them in the gift shop. The casino is a bit small in comparison to other casinos on the strip, but for me that was unimportant. There were plenty of dining options and entertainment options within the hotel, and if you're not careful you could end up spending your entire trip in the hotel. The carnegie deli is a must and the Cirque du soleil-Love show was amazing. The hotel staff were very friendly, the only complaint I have is the check-in took a very very long time. It was only our line though we noticed, we had a very slow woman behind the counter.The location could not be better, you are central on the strip and go either north or south and are within walking distance of many or all of the hotels depending on how much you're willing to walk. All in all I would definitely recommend this hotel to anyone staying in vegas, for the price I would say it offers the best value for your money on the strip.	
