Oct 13 2009	Love staying at Mirage	My sister and I stayed here for 6 nights on a special email offer I received. Our room had been completely updated and was very comfortable and beautiful. We had zero complaints about our room. I love that you can open the windows a bit at the Mirage to bring in fresh air. We were there in January so it was nice and cool and the air fresh. We did need to close the window at night though to keep out the traffic noise on the strip. The room was very quiet and we never heard a peep from any neighboring rooms. Checkin/checkout was a breeze with friendly staff at the ready. The only minor complaint is that it is a long trek from the parking garage to the elevators for the rooms. Because of the layout you have to walk all the way through reception and wind your way through the casino to get to the elevators, looping back to close to where you entered from the garage. If they had only put in a small hall.....sigh :-) But really, its a minor complaint. The Mirage is in a perfect center strip location where you can fill your days walking to all that your heart desires. We are returning for another stay next February. Viva Las Vegas!	
