Oct 8 2009 	Happy to return to the Mirage!	Stayed at the Mirage for 3 nights in September. I've been to Vegas many times and this was my first at the Mirage. The rooms were clean and spacious with comfortable bedding, plenty of storage for unpacking, very nice toiletries. You never had to wait for an elevator or be stuck in it while it stopped at every floor - which can be a nightmare in a crowded hotel. The casinos were also spacious and well ventilated; the smoke never got too bad. Restaurants were great!!! The Carnegie Deli is like being downtown Manhattan - a sight for sore eyes to this former New Yorker. The BLT Burger had some of the best burgers and milk shakes!! Their buffet also was excellent. Every dish we tried was VERY good. We were pleasantly surprised. There is a cafe by the pool which also served a nice lunch.The pool was lovely - expansive with plenty of seating and a nice way to relax for a few hours to get away from the hustle and bustle of Vegas. All staff we encountered were pleasant, friendly and helpful. The Beatles Love show was a wonderful treat and we heard great things about Terry Fator but were unable to get tickets this time around. At other hotels in Vegas, they give you a &quot;coupon book&quot; (if you will) that offers discounts for various restaurants, shops, and shows at the hotel. Makes sense to me - with all these choices in Vegas, why not give you an incentive to spend ALL your money at their facility? But not so with the Mirage. We would have liked some discount perhaps for the shows there, or their restaurants and attractions. (ie: animal habitat) Oh well.... The drinks at the lounges were pretty pricey. ($15 for a glass of house wine) For those of you who don't know Vegas, the Mirage is nicely located in easy walking distance of some of the nicer hotels to cruise through and see their attractions. On a scale of 1-10, with 10 being the plushest of the Vegas hotels, Mirage rates a 7 or 8. So it has a very nice feel to it. All in all, we were very happy with our choice to stay at the Mirage and would definitely return. If nothing else, we'll have to make it a point to have a meal at the Carnegie and a milk shake at the BLT!	
