Oct 6 2009 	The Mirage Hotel and Casino was FANTASTIC!!!	I recently stayed at The Mirage Hotel in Las Vegas, for 5 nights. We had a late check-in, as our flight didn't get in until 8pm. There were no lines at the check-in desk and the front desk staff there could not have been nicer. We got the non-smoking/2 Queen room that we asked for and it was lovely. The room and bathroom were very clean and tidy. The beds were the most comfortable that I have ever slept in. When I arrived back home, my own bed felt terrible after sleeping at the Mirage!!! Everyone there was very accomodating and couldn't do enough for you. We do not gamble, but I found the casino to be not as smokey as some, which is good since you have to walk through it to get to just about everything. The restaurants at the Mirage were very good, but also very expensive and the portions are huge. If you want to save money, it's best to share meals. The Carnegie Deli, for example, is wonderful, but the sandwiches could feed a family of 4 !!! Get one and split it, if you are not a big eater. The Paradise Cafe', by the pool area is very nice for Breakfast or Lunch. It is a beautiful setting and quieter than some of the restaurants inside the hotel. California Pizza Kitchen is great and a real bargain, if you do not want to spend an &quot;arm and a leg&quot; for a good meal. The pool there is beautiful, but arrive early if you want to find a lounge chair - it fills up fast. Don't miss the volcano, which is incredible! We were very impressed to see security guards at each elevator, in the evening, asking to see your room key, before they let you enter the elevator corridor. It made us feel very safe there. And last but certainly not least.... You must see Cirque du Soleil &quot;LOVE&quot; - it was unbelievable - words cannot describe how great it was!!!! It was definitely the highlight of our trip. The location of The Mirage is in the center of the strip, which is great, if you do not rent a car. Most of the tourist attractions are within walking distance. Be sure to see Madame Tussaud's wax museum, across the street at the Venetian. There is a monorail stop, across the street at Harrah's, which is very convienient, if you do not want to walk. The nice thing about the stop at Harrah's is that you do not have to walk a mile just to get to the monorail station - it's not too far from the entrance to Harrah's. I would highly recommend The Mirage if you want a great place to stay for a reasonable price.	
Oct 6 2009 	Would Stay Again	This was our 11th trip to Las Vegas and our first time at the Mirage. After reading some earlier reviews we were a little concerned, however there was no reason to be. We arrived around 10:30 a.m.,check-in was a breeze. We asked if we could have a strip view room and she said it wasn't ready yet, no problem we'll come back later. We came back around 3:00, the room was ready. Went to the room called for our luggage and it arrived in about 10 mins. The room was clean and updated. But as people have stated, the bathroom is quite small. When you open the bathroom door it almost hits the toilet. The bed was comfy but my husband and I weren't a huge fan of the pillows that everyone raves about. Actually my husband had a stiff neck the whole trip. All the other Vegas hotels we've stayed in have had floor to ceiling windows. The Mirage windows are more like a Holiday Inn window which gives more of a closed in feeling in the room. This is just my personal preference but not a deal breaker. The pool is beautiful but like everyone says people line up early. It doesn't open up until 8:00 but people start lining up at 7:15. People we were with who's room overlooked the pool saw one man in line at 6:10 every morning (a bit ridiculous). The casino is average, we didn't have any luck there. We ate at two of the hotel restaurants, California Pizza, it was okay but it was late so anything would be okay. The other was BLT, pretty decent burgers and much better than Burger Bar at Mandalay Bay where a burger can cost $22.00. All in all it's a good hotel and we would definately stay there again.	
