Oct 3 2009 	Fantastic in every aspect	My wife and I just returned from a 5 day stay at The Mirage. Booked a standard room online and the $20 trick worked to perfection for an upgrade to a 25th floor Towe Deluxe Room. Check in was around 8:00 pm on a Sunday evening and we had one person in line before us.Our room on arrival was clean and well stocked. The bed was fabulous which is key if you suffer from back pain like I do. Woke up every morning with no aches or pains in the back. The head was a different story some mornings.......Maid service was consistent every day. Bathroom was cleaned properly daily, however some people may not appreciate that shampoo/conditioner/body soap was not changed until empty. Did not bother us at all. Why unnecessarily waste??Two room issues: glass door in shower leaked. Leakage depended on which way the shower head was pointed. Small lake on floor first morning after first shower.Second issue: air conditioning is on motion sensor so when you wake up or return to the room it can be warm and stuffy. It cools down after some time.Location cannot be beat. We prefer the northern part of the strip so The Mirage was perfect for us.Food: ate at BLT burger our first night and it is highly recommended. Had the Cravings Buffet twice. Standard buffet fare. Nothing special. We are outside the casino most days.Casino: The casino is well laid out and easy to navigate. As a Canadian coming from a city witih a wide ranging smoking ban I did not find The Mirage's casino to be too bad in terms of smoke. I did well on the $1 video poker and the poker room is average in terms of how it is run. I almost missed my table call as there are no speakers outside the room.Pool: really separates The Mirage from most other strip properties. It is large and beautiful. On warm/hot days it can be hard to locate chairs as people reserve them with towels and it is crowded but what do you expect froma hotel with 3,044 rooms and most of the clientele being sun seekers? The chairs pushed together are an annoyance but they are wide so it is not like you are bumping nasties with your neighbour. Later in the afternoon is the time to go.$15/day internet charges are annoying but rather standard now in higher range hotels.Checkout was a breeze. We went down mid morning to settle the tab and waited in line for 3 minutes at most. Paid our tab and the gentleman at the desk said to keep keys on us until noon then leave in room. This allowed an extra 90 mins to walk around and enjoy the hotel.All in all The Mirage is a top quality hotel that you can get discounts on by signing up online for e-mail deals. I highly recommend this hotel to anyone looking for a nicer than average hotel room and Vegas experience.	
