Sep 28 2009 	Beautiful hotel	We chose the Mirage the hotel for our honeymoon. From check-in to (reluctant) departure, the hotel does everything a fine establishment is supposed to do. The hotel is well-maintained (an amazing feat given the 24-hour nature of the place) and offers an excellent location with proximity to the rest of the strip. It was stated that the pool is the best of all the major hotels; I have no reason to think otherwise. We're not much on the gambling, but there appears to be be nothing missing from the choices at the hotel. Two hamburgers and two drinks came to $50 with tip at the BLT Burger. It was all the encouragement I needed to go elsewhere for all other meals. The Mirage would do itself a favor by lowering prices in the restaurants; it would keep more of its guests venturing to other establishments. All things considered, it is an excellent hotel.	
Sep 28 2009 	Do not look anywhere else - the Mirage has everything and more!	Just got back from 7 nights at the Mirage with my Wife. We have been to Vegas several times before and stayed in the Venetian and MGM. The Mirage is by far the best! There is a great selection of restaurants ranging from good value Pizza to fine dining and lots of good bars and clubs. The pool is delightful although it does get busy. If you are going over the weekend I would recommend reserving a poolside lounger for $50 USD. It is well worth it as you can rock up any time you like, the chairs are more comfortable than the normal ones and you can settle up your drinks/food bill at the end rather than every time you get a drink. Plus, you get a great location by the pool. The best thing thing overall is the atmosphere in the Mirage. It is really great and in my opinion makes this by far the best place to stay. It may cost more than some of the other hotels on the strip - but when you're going to Vegas - why not splash out and make it one to remember!	
Sep 27 2009 	Oasis in the Dessert	We stayed at the Mirage the same weekend as the Mayweather fight. Overall, we had a great experience. We arrived after 9 pm on Thursday night, so they had run out of deluxe king rooms. We were offered either a deluxe queen room or a handicap accessible room. We took the accessible room, with an understanding that they would call us when a deluxe king with a strip view became available the next day. I would definitely recommend doing the room change rather than staying in the accessible room for your entire trip. The accessible room did not have quite as many of the upgrades found in the other remodeled rooms. Plus, it didn't have any counter space in the bathroom. The room move went smoothly. We just had to call before 4 pm the next day. When we called down for the change, they changed our keys for us and told us that we were moving to a room on the same floor. We were moved to room 21076, and it was an awesome room. I wouldn't say as much for the room service. My husband's sandwhich was way better than my pasta. If you do order room service, you only need one order because the portions are huge. We only went to the pool for a short time, but it was really nice. We went in the late afternoon, so there were plenty of seats available. When we left, we went to the Secret Garden to see the white tigers. We went around 5:30, which was the perfect time. All of the animals were really active. Two of the younger tigers were play fighting in their pond. We also got to see the trainers grooming one of the large males. All five of the dolphins were in the pools while we were there. I thought that it was well worth the $15. We only ate at one of the restaurants. We would highly recommend BLT Burger. The casino was nice. I would probably think that it was nicer if we had won. We had a great stay, and the hotel was in a great location. I would definitely stay here again.	
