Sep 13 2009 	Expensive****	I looked and read loads of reviews and this one being the Mirage had some of the best reviews so we went with it. My husband and I stayed in Sept(will never go in Sept again) way to hot! we stayed three nights. The rooms were fine,bed very comfy but that was about it besides the Beatles Love show that we just loved. First day there we ate at BLT Burger in the Mirage,$38.00 mind you and two of the worst hamburgers we have ever ate,what a rip off but yet you will see it packed in there. The reason is the food all around you is expensive in the main big hotels. Go across the street to Imperial Palace for the buffet or Harrahs buffet for $14.99,we even had a late night hamburger at McDonalds across the street. Check the Las Vegas booklet in your room for coupons,there is even Denneys across the street,much cheaper and does the trick. We spent the most there strictly on food for the most part. Go down to the Sahara and get a dollar hotdog,$1.00 shot of whatever you want and keep the glass. You have to look around for cheap food and when your walking everything seems far. Take the bus that goes along the strip for $7.00 for a 24 hour pass and jump on that for travel. The weather was 101 and very very humid, over 75 degrees at night. Best month to go would be in winter months. The Love show is a must,you will not believe it...all I can say is wow....That's what made my vacation well worth it. Next time I'm going to stay at the Flamingo as it is in the heart of a lot. Just do not eat at the Mirage...the food sucks for the price. Room is fine and don't forget Ben &amp; Jerry's Ice Cream across the street for something sweet,there is coupons for this out there also. Look around for places to eat much cheaper then inside of Hotel.	
Sep 11 2009 	Very Good Large 	I travelled to Vegas with an all-male group of friends and had a great time. The Mirage is situated in the middle of the Strip and it's location could not be better. Upon arrival, we were met with the largest lobby reception area I have ever seen and also the busiest too as you need to go through part of the Casino and restaurant area to get to the check-in area. The check-in was quick and easy and the rooms were superb and bigger then I expected. One mention... do not use the Mini-Bar at all because it is mega expensive and even charges you even if you have removed an item just to look at it !! Obviouisly when visting Vegas, the casino ifs part of the trip and I honestly thought that the Casino in the Mirage was the biggest and best of the lot. The pool area is big and clean but you need to be up very early in order to get a sunbed (Towels are free of charge). The Hotel Spa was also good and relaxation was definitely required after another late night. I can only really complain about one thing in the hotel and that was the Chinese Restaurant... the decor was great, the staff were pleseant but the meal was a shocker... I've been to a lot of restaurants in my time but this meal was the pits... tasteless was being kind to it. If you visit Las Vegas, definitely stay at the Mirage because I would have no hesitation in staying there again.	
