y hot, take the time to go to the one on the state border.Las Vegas is an adult resort and folks will put cards in your hands as you are walking down the strip at night adverting women, in fact a large van drives past advertsing ' a women to you hotel room ring this number'The Bellagio fountains are a must every 15 minutes, at night.If you want to gamble be careful, they give you free drinks at the tables if you are gambling...get you drunk and you spend more.Take time to visit Freemont Street at night, five blocks are covered with a screen which every hour plays something, it is amazing. This is a the old strip and a cab ride from the Mirage cost us $40.There are loads of shops( designer and otherwise) along the strip but they are not that cheap.You get a cab from the front of Hotel there is a queue and a bellman, talk to them about what you want to do,they are very good, also one day he mentioned that it was cheaper for our party of ten to take a limo, instead of two cabs, great during the day but at night it is not the case.We stopped for five nights and that was it for us. Have fun	
