Sep 8 2009 	Not just a Mirage!	I recently stayed in Vegas for the first time for a weekend with one of my best girlfriends. We chose the Mirage since it had such a convenient location at center strip and found a very competitive price on priceline.com. We were not disappointed! Had a wonderful time. The concierge were very helpful in booking tickets for Love, their cirque du soleil show in house, and even assisted in providing free passes to Jet and other clubs on the strip. The rooms were very nice, modernly furnished, and clean. The pool area was incredible - a little crowded on Saturdays and difficult to find a lounger at times, but the waterfalls at the pool were very nice and poolside waitress service was excellent. They even have a topless pool area, called Bare. The dining inside the hotel was incredible as well. We ate at the buffet Cravings, which pleasantly surprised me as buffets go!, and Stack, which had incredible steak. The clubs Revolution and Jet were both quite good - although getting into Jet was a little more of a pain. Revolution, a Beatles inspired club, had very fun decore and offered free vodka drinks to ladies on Friday nights (very much appreciated!)I could not have had a better first time experience in Vegas, and I will most definitely return to the Mirage in future Vegas trips. You could quite literally have a fantastic time and never leave the hotel!!	
