has the same menu (and owned by the same group) as Stack at the Mirage. Fix was AMAZING!! I wish I could remember everything everyone in our group had, but I can not! Everyone had something different and not a single person had anything bad to say! A few girls also had California Pizza Kitchen and The Deli and said they were good as well. Pool: We never made it to the 'main' Mirage pool. A group of 7 girls in their mid-20's draws alot of attention for the promoters. So we were walked into Bare each day that we came downstairs in our suits. They knew us by name by the end of the weekend... Anyways, the first day we got down there, they told us we could have a set of sunbeds until someone pays for them. We ordered drinks and instantly got in the pool. It was unusually quiet, especially after hearing the promoters compare the atmosphere to &quot;ReHab&quot; at the Hard Rock on Sundays. We later found out that the main pool's chlorine tank had exploded and for safety precautions, they had to stop the music. Everyone was very friendly at the pool and we had a great time (we were actually able to talk to people since it was so quiet!). And no, not a single one of us enjoyed it as a 'European Pool' Experience, although MANY of the other guests did. By the end of the day, the music was turned back on and it was a great party atmosphere. However, it was a bit crowded due to the tank exploding. The next day, there was no issue with exploding tanks so there was music and was less crowded.Club: Again, group of 7 girls.... While checking into the room, we were approached by the Jet club promoters. We were put on their Girls VIP list for that night. They had free drinks for girls until midnight, so we thought, why not? It was a BIT confusing once we got down to get into the club though. There were about 3 different lines going, and we were told to go from one place to another for a while. Once we were in the right line (after about 5 minutes of walking from here to there) it only took us about 10 minutes to get in, which is much better than the other lines. The club was packed, but they played good music. The drinks were good and strong, made better by the fact they were free!All and all, it was an amazing weekend. The Mirage was at the perfect location. The rooms were roomy, beds were comfy, and it was a great experience!	
