Aug 17 2009	I love the Mirage!	I won a trip via a Southwest Airline's Twitter contest and ended up at the Mirage! It was awesome! Probably would never have stayed there since I earn comps with Harrah's.The location was great and getting around to the strip was simple. Check in was a little wait but the staff could not have been friendlier!Little bit of a walk to the room but a straight shot and lots of shopping. We had a lovely view of the strip.The room was clean and very well appointed! Very contemporary. Beds were comfy. (pictures attacehed) The windows bugged me because they needed to be washed but not that big of deal..Housekeeping service was timely and excellent.Lots of fun touristy shopping, lots of eating options and bars. Walked around the pool and it looked so nice!Nice buffet...albiet a little pricey. Very nice stay! Thanks Southwest and Mirage!	
Aug 17 2009 	A great place to stay	My husand, two sons (21 and 17) and I stayed at the Mirage in Las Vegas from 12th July for a week. On arrival at reception of course the first thing you see is the famous aquarium - it is amazing. On checking we requested a room with a bit of a view. No problem. My husband and I were given a room on the 15th floor overlooking the volcano and the strip. My sons were allocated a room on the 11th floor looking over towards the Rio Hotel and the mountains in the distance (sun sets were great). Perfect views. Although the place never sleeps - we did - did not hear a sound. We had breakfast in the Caribe Cafe every morning - great selection. We ate dinner in this restaurant once - food was lovely, we also ate at the BLT Burger, Paradise Cafe and the California Pizza Kitchen. If there was a fault it was that the plates were too big and too full!! The hotel was excellent and we all thoroughly enjoyed our stay. The rooms were spotless. They were cleaned with new bedding and towels daily. The staff were very helpful and friendly. There were loads of loungers at the pool and on the four or so occasions we stayed by the pool it did not take us too long to find loungers. People did leave towels on the loungers of course - where doesn't this happen, but the staff were very good at going round all the areas regularly and taking towels away where there were no other belongings and it was obvious the people had left. So, there was always a supply of loungers no matter when you went to the pool.Loved the hotel and would go back in a minute.	
Aug 17 2009 	Great Room Excellent Location	Apparently The Mirage is the resort that started the mega resort trend, I can see why. The rooms are great -- newly remodeled with an amazing bed (big down comforter and pillows). The bathroom is a little small, but that's ok. The shower head is AWFUL -- that's my only complaint -- it's a super low-flow model. The pool is great. Plenty of space for everyone and the water is the perfect temperature. Casino has everything you expect, and it's quite large. The location is perfect -- right in the middle of the strip. Overall, this was a great stay and we're really looking forward to visiting The Mirage again.	
Aug 15 2009 	My birthday disappoinment at The Mirage	My family and I arrived around 1am after a long and delayed flight to Las Vegas to find that our rooms were not available and given away to someone else. We were celebrating my fathers and my birthday and our first adult family trip together!! At booking, we were promised two renovated, double bed, non-smoking and adjoining rooms. We were given one two double bed, older room that smelled like smoke and the other room was an updated king, which was nice. My Mother did not sleep in the older smoke smelling room because she had asthma. After discussing with the staff at check in that this is not what were we promised she did consider to accommodate us to the rooms and to be moved the next day. However, that was a complete mess as well! My mother and I had to hang out around the hotel all day to wait for the front desk to contact us on our hotel phone to let us know when it was time to change rooms. After touching base with the check-in staff, they still did not have the correct rooms, adjoining and strip view that was promised. About 4pm we were finally switched but had to move our luggage from both room ourselves, which I thought they should have offered to handle. The keys given to us for both new rooms did not work. We then had to wait for Security to come let us in our new rooms. After contacting the desk again and 45 minutes later, the Concierge finally delivered our new keys. That was a whole day wasted!! Instead of celebrating my birthday we stayed in the room waiting to hear from the staff!! We were finally able to go sight seeing on the strip. One of the rooms also had no bath mat or hand towels. I can say that the beds were very comfortable.At booking, we were also informed that we would receive a $50 Cravings Buffet Credit and 4 Secret Garden passes per each room. On Sunday morning we went down to the Cravings Buffet and again there was an issue! We stood in line for a while and when we gave our card and room number there was no credit. The cashier had to contact the front desk and we held up the line. The bad thing about it, the time was changing from breakfast to lunch and the people behind us that were in line were frustrated as well. They went ahead and fixed our credit for breakfast. The food was bland and not that good! After breakfast, we went to the Secret Garden and again there was an issue. I was totally over it by now! The lady at the desk for the Garden went ahead and let us in. The Secret Garden was pretty cool and we enjoyed it. The night before we left on Monday night, I spoke with the front desk manager about everything we had experienced during our trip. She apologized and informed us that the front staff that told us there was adjoining rooms was new and in training. She credited back our card for the Cravings Buffet and made sure we were not charged additionally for the Secret Garden. She first was going to credit some money back for one night stay and we asked for the total for one night for one room was credited. She was nice and handled it but by this time we had been frustrated and were flying out the next day.My family and I arrived around 1am after a long and delayed flight to Las Vegas to find that our rooms were not available and given away to someone else. We were celebrating my fathers and my birthday and our first adult family trip together!! At booking, we were promised two renovated, double bed, non-smoking and adjoining rooms. We were given one two double bed, older room that smelled like smoke and the other room was an updated king, which was nice. My Mother did not sleep in the older smoke smelling room because she had asthma. After discussing with the staff at check in that this is not what were we promised she did consider to accommodate us to the rooms and to be moved the next day. However, that was a complete mess as well! My mother and I had to hang out around the hotel all day to wait for the front desk to contact us on our ho