Aug 13 2009 	Great place will definitely go back	Stayed for 4 nights at the Mirage in a Towever premium room (on the 25th floor) from Aug 3rd to 7th. Check in around noon was fast and efficient. It it too bad that they have individual lines instead of one big line that takes you to the next available teller, but it was fairly quick. (I would expect it to be worse on weekends).Room was very nice, facing the pool (as requested). You could see all the main hotels like Paris, Ceasar's, Planet Hollywood, etc.. Plus you could also see the highway and mountains in the back. I was very quiet and didn't hear my neighbours or people in the hall at all.TV was massive with something that looked like a 46&quot; LCD. It had HD channels (in the 100's), but they never worked at the signal in my room was week. I called housekeeing, but it never gt fixed.Bathroom was very nice with whirlpool tub and separate shower (With amazing pressure!) and 2 sinks. Plenty of towels, soap, etc..Ate at the Buffet for breakfast and at the pool restaurant once for lunch and also once for breakfast. (Breakfast at the pool restaurant was fairly expensive for what I got, but it was great eating outside).Pool was crowded for weekdays. Finding chairs at 8:15 was no problem, but after 9am can start becoming difficult. Not many people reserved chairs and left, for the most part, they were all occupied even that early in the morning. (When it's 100+ degrees, you want to enjoy the morning hours)Checkout was fast as well.I really enjoyed my stay and would definitely go back there. IThe stay was pretty much perfect!	
Aug 13 2009 	Fabulous Stay at the Mirage Hotel 	Trip to Vegas for a Stagette weekend (July 25-28), with 5 girls.Booked our flights with Allegiant seperately from the hotel and got a great deal.Having stayed at the Monte Carlo in Vegas previously (which was fine), the Mirage far exceeded my expectations. Especially since we got a great nightly rate, which included passes to the Secret Garden (4), and a $40 dining credit.The hotel was packed, and 100% sold for the weekend, great vibe there too.Check-in was efficient. We had requested two rooms with 2 Queens, but they were unavailable when we arrived.However the hotel had us in rooms with 1 King bed, and had a Queen sized cot delivered within minutes of getting into our rooms, they were also able to keep us a few doors down from each other on the same floor, even though the rooms were booked seperately and at different times.The next day they informed us that they had been able to snag two rooms with 2 Queen beds, that were adjoining- this change was done very quickly for us, and at no extra charge.The room decor is lovely, nice flat panel televisions, and very comfy duvets/pillows.Housekeeping was excellent as well- rooms were very clean.The pool at the Mirage is beautiful- it was so busy, that we had a hard time finding a chair, but it was so hot you needed to be in the water anyway.Poolside service was also excellent.Checked out Bare (topless pool), because the main pool was so crowded, and the first day at Bare was excellent, great crowd, and you don't have to be topless to be in there, so we had a great time in a more adult environment.Hit Bare the second day, and the crowd this time was super snobby, and unfriendly.What appeared to be a swingers group became offended that we wouldnt take our tops off (despite the other dozen women there with their bathing suits on), and kept questioning us about it, and staring at us and whispering- very odd experience.So beware Bare, the second day we were there, there weren't just harmless topless women, this group was being obscene, and fondling each other, and other nasty-ness in the pool. (unfortunately this group was quite unsightly too, which made it even worse!).Other than this weird, unpleasant experience with this group from California, we encountered nice/friendly people all over the resort, including the staff.The Secret Garden/Dolphin Habitat was really nice, lots of animals, kids would love it.We checked out the following restaurants:1. Carnagie Deli- portions sizes were astronimical. Wouldn't go back since its fairly expensive, and no one should be able to eat sandwhiches that size! But it was good fresh ingredients, and good service.2. California Pizza- great service, except for a nasty hostess, also very weird. The servers were fantastic though, and the food was tasty.3. Caribe (I think that is what is called): excellent breakfast, and reasonably priced; also amazing service. One morning we saw Keifer Sutherland eating in there, and harassed him for his pic (felt pretty bad bothering him at breakfast, but one of my friends was insistent).The nightclub inside the Mirage (Jet) was also great- great service, good crowd.Just find one of the promoters in the lobby during the day, and get on the guest list- no waiting, no cover.In short the Mirage Hotel was an exceptional place to in Vegas, and I would head back there for sure.	
