Aug 12 2009 	i can now say I have been to Vegas.	I do not get away much- wanted to go someplace different for my 25th Anniversary. SInce I am in the business- I decided Las Vegas had gotten a bum rap and I wanted to support them. After much searching, I choose the Mirage. The hotel itself was fine. Eventhough I told them who I was and why I was there- I got one of the older rooms with no few( I would never do that to an industry person). Hoover Dam trip was great. Loved theVenitian Shops and the Gondola Ride. i recommend you buy a bus pass and take the bus up and down the strip. You really do not need a car. I think the next time I would stay downtown- the real people stay there. Pool at Mirage was nice - not hard to get a seat at all. Staff said business has been picking up. The best service we had was at Outback on the Strip - waiter was great. never made a restaurant reservation - was able to get in everywhere. Well, I can now say I have been to Vegas.	
Aug 12 2009 	Great Hotel	Its really hard to choose between all the wonderful looking hotels in this lively place but we decided on the Mirage because of its location (equal distance from the Stratosphere and the Mandalay Bay at either end of the strip). The pool area was wonderful with great service all day and the various resturants were all good quality and value for money. Unfortunately, some of the rooms were being refurbished so we were awoken daily at 7am by the builders hammering and drilling in the room directly above ours. Also the 'volcano' attraction at the front of the hotel was closed for maintenance for the whole of our stay. Overall the hotel/casino was very clean and comfortable and theservice we recieved was very good. I would stay here again as long as the refurb was finished.	
Aug 12 2009 	Excellent Stay at the Mirage!	My husband and I have been to Vegas three times now. This is by far the best hotel we have stayed at!! Everything is right there that you could possibly want.Transportation from airport- last 2 times we took the shuttle and although it is cheap ($6.50 each I think) it is painful if you aren't one of the first stops as you wait at each hotel for everyone to get on or off. We took a cab this time for $20 on the wya to the hotel and for some reason only $15 on the way back to the airport (2 different routes of course). Definitely worth the cab fare!!!Check in - Very fast and the lady was extremely friendly and helpful. Our Room - Better than we expected, we were in a deluxe room on the 19th floor with a great view of the Strip! We had 2 dressers and although we were only there 5 days it is nice to be able to unpack and get organized. There is a mini bar in the room but unless you want to pay premium prices don't touch anything in it...it charges by weight so as soon as you move something it will be automatically billed to your room. Our bathroom was spacious and really clean. We had a king size bed and a comfy chair for 2 to sit on and look out at the strip as well as watch the volcano show. There is a large plasma tv on the wall as well but we didn't use it.Restaurants - You can not leave without ordering a corned beef or pastrami sandwich at Carnegie Deli but be prepared to share it...it would be impossible for one person...actually even two to eat it all!! Stack has great food as well and we also tried happy hour appetizers at Japanois that were tasty. Otherwise we ate at other places on the strip. You have to go to Margaritaville just across the road by the Flamingo even if you just go to check it out...go all the way upstairs and there is a balcony where you can sit and look out at everyone walking the strip...you usually don't have to wait for a table up there and I am pretty sure lot's of people don't know about it. Regardless of what you order and where you eat be sure to check out the portion sizes...they were so huge everywhere we went we shared all the time. Not sure how anyone can eat portions that large!! Oh well...you are on vacation!! :)The pool- really nice pool...we stayed at the Flamingo before and it's a different environment. Can't really say which pool is nicer as they are both great. The Mirage is a little more crowded together but has more loungers than the Flamingo...the Flmaingo was a little louder and younger so it was fun too. There are drinks and a nice little patio restaurant there but again...huge portions and they charge you $5 to share. Our waiter suggested buying a $3 fruit plate and they don't charge you the $5 sharing fee and at least you get something for the $3. Turned out the fruit plate was really great.Casino - not the most fun atmosphere I have had in a casino but then again we didn't win anything so that might have been why! We did win at the Flamingo this time as well as last time quite often so you went up and down but at least you had fun. They definitely come around with drinks at the Mirage more than I have seen at other casino's.Freemont Street-in our other trips to Vegas we never went but decided to grab a cab and head over there to check it out. I wouldn't go back again but it was definitely a fun thing to go and see. Would suggest anyone who has not gone to go and check it out.Shopping - of course the outlet mall (the outdoor one not the one by the airport) is fantastic with lot's of different stores and great deals. If you don't feel like going that far though the Fashion mall is just past Treasure Island and also has some great stores and good deals.Fitness Centre - I checked around before we went and and apparently they don't have one so I didn't bring my workout gear. Really though with all the walking you do it's no biggie.Check out - again no issues and they held our bags for us as had to check out 4 hours before we had to go to the airport.If you have any questions don't hesitate to contact me...it was a great stay...I just wouldn't hang out too long at their casino.	
Aug 12 2009 	Excellent hotel	We celebrated our 42nd anniversary on August 5th by taking an offer from the Mirage. We have been going to Las Vegas every year for the past 18 years. We were pleasantly surprised in all catagories. The Mirage is a great hotel.The room was clean and the bed was extremely comfortable. Had to request face cloths twice during our stay. There was also an unusual noise from the drains in the bathroom. This was a surprise considering the cleanliness of the room and the general maintainance of the room and hallways.I would like to commend the staff for the security in the evening. To access the elevators you had to show your room key. We were on a card floor, so it even gave you a more secured feeling knowing the hotel uses extra measures to protect guest.The location, salon, pool, and rest. were all great.We were placed on the 25th floor as an upgrade. The room was 25058 and the view was magnificent.The Mirage is rated number one on my list above Belagio or the Monte Carlo. We will return next year for our 43rd. Casino slots were not paying off so we ended up going to other casinos to gamble.	
