Aug 11 2009 	Great Hotel For The Money	Just returned from a 4 day stay at The Mirage and loved the property. I was traveling as part of a group of 25 friends and it proved to be a great choice for our visit to Vegas.We booked standard view rooms so there wasn't much to see but we really didn't spend much time in our room anyway and I don't think I looked out of the window more than once or twice. The room size was big enough to be comfortable and the bathroom was more than adequate. Nice large flat-screen tv and an in-room safe were great. What can you ask for when you are paying $69 a night over a weekend?Restaurants were very good though all of the prime choices closed at 10p.m. We partied at BarePool each day and needed some power naps afterwards so the 10p.m. dinner thing was annoying. We ended up in the deli twice and I am not a huge fan of deli sandwiches when a big steak or some sushi should have been available. Oh well though - the Cravings Buffet was good for breakfast.BarePool is possibly one of the craziest pools in the country. Wow - expensive but totally worth it. Cover was $40 for men and $20 for ladies (though many ladies had comp passes) and you have a $50 minimum to sit in a lounge chair on Mon-Fri ($100 on Sat or Sun) but it is worth it. Fun people just having a good time and it was nice to be surrounded by adults as my group of friends and I wanted to catch up without kids running all over the place. I would forget a cabana unless you are looking for privacy as they sit back too far from the pool itself. The Casino was more than adequate with a good-sized Sports Book which is perfect for the upcoming football season.Enjoyed Dos Caminos (Mexican Restaurant) across the street at the Palazzo. Great food and a lively place to eat. Lavo is a fun choice if you are tired of Pure, TAO, Tryst etc..In all would return in a minute!	
Aug 9 2009 	Exceeded our expectations!!!	My husband stayed at the Mirage for the first time, and after staying there, I am sure we will return! From the time we checked in until we checked out, we found the Mirage more than accommodating in all areas. The room was beautiful, chic and huge! The bed was sooooo comfortable, we did not want to get up! We decided to spend a day at the pool and went down at 9:00 am, which we thought would be plenty of time to find a chair...WRONG! It seems the game to play is to go down to the pool at 6:00 am and throw a towel and a book or newspaper on the chair you want and go back to bed, then you come back down hours later. That way, people ARE reserving their spot, but not at an additional charge (there is a $50 charge to reserve a chair). I think the people that do this are rude and this should be discouraged and/or stopped by the hotel. It ruins it for us that just want to play by the rules. The pool is wonderful, lush and very tropical. We finally did find a chair and had a great day at the pool! I also went to their spa and had a hot stone massage...OMG!!! It was awesome and their spa is the best I have been to, it would rival any out their and I have been to numerous spa's. Try it out, it won't dissapoint. We loved everything about the Mirage and we will return ASAP!!	
