Aug 4 2009 	Amazing superb!...	Me and my parents stayed at the Mirage hotel &amp; casino in 2006, and can not recommend this hotel more highly!. Situated in the middle of the Las Vegas strip, the mirage is home to an erupting volcano, dolphins, elephants and Sigfreud &amp; Roys white tigers. This hotel is not as large as some of the nearby resorts such as the MGM grand where it feels like you have to walk through Lakeside to get from your room to the pool! The Mirage is truly breathtaking!, when you check in you are greeted by an incredible aquarium and the indoor tropical rainforest is amazing. You have to walk through the casino to leave the hotel and to get to your room but this is only Vegas's way of trying to get you to have a flutter on the machines. The mirage is home to one of the most famous shows in the world - The Sigfreud &amp; Roy magic show! Unfortunately we did not get to see the show as it was around the time when Roy nearly had his head bitten off ! The resort has many bars and restaurants if you do not feel like venturing out onto the famous strip. The surrounding areas to the hotel is fabulous and encloses dolphins, and Sigfreud &amp; Roys secret garden which houses African elelphants and tigers just to name a few! The rooms are spacious yet cosy, they all have a television and hairdryer etc. Overall, we thoroughly enjoyed visiting Las Vegas and the Mirage and i definently plan on returning with my husband in the near future !	
