Jul 26 2009 	Great value location and clean property. Awesome pool.	Booked the room about 6 months ago with a great promotion. The whole week was $550 for a regular renovated room. When we arrived, I tried the infamous '$20 trick' at the front desk. It worked like a charm. Got upgraded to the 25th floor (highest floor for regular-non-suite-rooms) with a strip and pool view. They also left a bottle of bubbly in the room too. The room was recently renovated and modern. A large Flat Panel TV is in a perfect spot on the wall. The bathrooms in the high floors are larger than a standard room which is great. They also have a jacuzzi tub. (Try the $20 trick). Housekeeping kept the room clean for the week we where there...with only a few exceptions. One day...they forgot to leave us new soap and shampoo. Another day they forgot to leave us hand towels. There were housekeepers in the hall at all hours...so we just asked for them. Not a big deal.The A/C units are strange. We like COLD rooms. It almost looked like there is a motion sensor on the control. It was always warm when we returned...but cooled off once we were there for an hour or so.The pool is really nice. You have to get there early if you want a good spot. All waterfalls were working and the water was nice and cool. Note that the pool closes at 8 PM...I guess they want you to go in and eat and gamble. Oh...didn't make it to the 'Bare' pool, but could see it from our room. Didn't look like there were too many 'topless' guests. Kind of think it's a bit too gimmiky. Restaurants in Mirage:Cravings Buffet: Ate here for Sunday Brunch. The price without alcohol is about $20 per person. It was NOT worth the money. Most of the regular lunch items were replaced with cereal and oatmeal and eggs. I know...this is Brunch...but the overall quality of the offerings wasn't up to the 'upscale' food offerings that Vegas is pushing. The sweets section was a bit sad as well. Not many choices and it all tasted like it was pre-made and brought in. The service was SLLLLOOOW too...Even with a soda and a water...we often found our glasses empty with dirty plates on our table. BLT Burger: This is a new spot for the Mirage. It replaces the White Tiger exhibit at the entrance of the casino. With all they hype and previous reviews...I expected a great meal. It was busy so we sat at the bar. The bartender gave us menus and asked what we wanted to drink. TIP- Order WATER first! They have combos that include burger, fries and a shake or drink. This way...if you want a shake...you are not stuck with a soda or other drink you don't want. Also, the combos are only with the 'classic' burger. So if you want a bacon cheese burger...you'll have to order everything separately. For 2 burgers, 2 fries and 2 sodas...the bill came to over $40!! CRAZY! The fries were typical hotel fries. I bet they serve the same ones in the Mirage Cafe. The burger was 'good'...not really done to the 'medium' I ordered. The bun was not 'fresh'...or didn't seem special. The great part was that the lettuce &amp; tomato were cold...and the burger was hot. Also...the burger meat wasn't that special either. Not worth the $40 we spent.After those 2 restaurants...we decided to eat elsewhere. The good thing is that the Mirage is centrally located...so there is food options very close by. The casino is your typical Vegas casino. Everything you can image. The atrium is nice with a very tropical feel. The drink service in the casino was great...I think Mirage had the best drink service on the strip. It seemed like a girl was by every 10 minutes asking if we wanted a drink. While the slots seemed a bit tighter than other properties on the strip...we did have a good few days. But since slots are all luck...who knows. Didn't make it to their nightclub Jet...or Revolution. Kind of clubbed out....they all seem to be the same after a while. Why pay the cover and for the overpriced drinks?Would stay here again without a second thought...would just eat elsewhere.	
Jul 26 2009 	Crowded and hot	Just back from Las Vegas and have to say no complaints about the Mirage hotel except like all the other hotels, the food is all way overpriced. I have been to Las Vegas before and have never seen it this crowded, esp. considering it is the dead heat of summer! So crowded, you can barely walk up and down the strip; you spend all of your time dodging in and out among masses of people and can only really go at night as it is too hot during the day. Loved the pools at the Mirage; spent all day every day by the pools. You have to &quot;save&quot; your pool chairs though or you simply won't get any. We had to get down there before 9am or there weren't any 2 chairs left next to each other. Don't just leave your towels though or someone else will take them; we left a beach bag and books on our chairs so it was obvious someone was using them. There is a McDonalds across the street which we ended up at for most of our meals because it is so expensive to eat anywhere else! Walking up and down the strip takes forever and is not as simple as it looks; you can't always cross the street where you want; sometimes you have to go over walkways and around or through hotels to get where you want. It is a LOT of walking! The hotels look close together but you quickly learn it is a long walk between each one. There is a monorail but it doesn't go to every hotel and sometime you are still quite a distance away from where you want to go when you get off and it costs $5.00 per person one way. We thought this would be a fun and inexpensive getaway and instead it was quite expensive and not so much fun! I guess it is what you make of it though. I would recommend going when it is not so hot and maybe during a holiday when most people will be at home with family, like Thanksgiving or Christmas.	
Jul 26 2009 	Overall a Great Trip	My husband and I just came back from 4 days/3 nights at the Mirage. I have been to Vegas before, staying at MGM, Paris and Wynn. The Mirage is my #2 choice now after staying there (Wynn being the best).Our check-in was long, there weren't alot of people on the desk but we were lucky as we arrived around 11am and our room was ready right then. We asked for a strip view which we got BUT being on the 7th floor couldn't see a panoramic view of the strip, we could see some of the volcano though.Overall the hotel was excellent, yes there is a lot of walking but that's what you do in Vegas. Our room was good for us, we didn't spend much time in it; the bathroom was beautiful but again small, however it was perfect for us.We ate at BLT Burger, Cravings for breakfast and Stack - all were excellent but pricey. At Stack, like many other Mirage restaurants, ask for the Prix Fix menu (even if they don't give it to you when you sit). The portions are large and the price is more tolerable.The pool was beautiful, busy but it was also 100+ degrees. 32oz drinks there cost $16 so beware. Good thing - you can charge it all to your room.I would definately recommend the Mirage again and would most likely stay there - great location on the strip, good rooms and atmosphere. Also, don't miss LOVE!!	
