Jul 25 2009 	Pool Location 	My cousin and I booked two, two bedroon penthouse suites, for a Wednesday and Thursday night. His family of 8 in one, my family of 6 in another. The front desk gave us the run around a bit when we checked in. Check in was supposed to be at 3:00. We actually could have had suites at that time, but we held out for an hour and a half in order to get strip views. Be forewarned that if you are going for a specific view, it seems requesting when you make the reservation has no value. You will be assigned your view when you get there. We had a couple roll-aways brought up. The suite was very nice. They have not been refurbished like most of the rest of the hotel, but my wife and I prefer the older decor. It's more plush. The floor to ceiling windows were covered with a screen to advertise the &quot;Love&quot; show for the hotel and it obscured our view a bit and made it nearly impossible to take decent photos of the fabulous view. Our previous stay in Las Vegas was the Bellagio, also in a two bedroom suite. We decided on the mirage because of a savings of four to five-hundred dollars a night on very similar rooms. My daughter was looking up the star ratings for the various strip resorts, and came up with an interesting observation. None of the 5 star resorts have ads on their actual building, the strictly use their marquees. It's too bad Mirage is covering their best rooms with ad screens. No big deal. Our view was still great. 30th floor.The service overall was excellent. Both suites had air conditioning problems when arrived. A phone call brought up an engineer almost immediately. The same with requesting extra robes and roll away beds. Quick and friendly employees.Thursday morning, we rented a poolside cabana. We were early enough to pick pretty much any on we wanted. We really enjoyed spending the day there, very relaxing. The pool is one of the top pools in Vegas IMHO. Bellagio was too formal for my taste. I prefer a tropical type atmosphere. We ate both nights at the Cravings Buffet. It was fine. For this hotel, a good value. One of the perks of having a suite is front of the line passes. Everything we tried was good to excellent, as was the service. We didn't try any of the other places on property to eat.We don't gamble, but the casino seemed smokier that when I had been here in the past and the foot traffic going to and coming from the rooms to the front door, seems never-ending,The volcano is worthwhile checking out, but the best thing going on the strip is the fountains of Bellagio.	
