Jul 21 2009 	As good as any 4-5 star hotel I've stayed in	Spent 3 days at the Mirage in June at the end of a Utah National Parks tour. We booked a room in the top two floors. The check in took only about 15 minutes at 4PM. The room was very high up and overlooked the pool, which we used almost immediately. It's a very nice pool and renting a float was well worth it. The King bed, and the large custom bathroom, as well as the spiffy fresh decor and the love seat, were all eccellent. Having 2 closets, one next to each side of the bed was a nice touch. There wasn't a price list for the minibar, and we asked the bellhop and he warned us it was pricey .. but we never got the menu so didn't use. We were never disturbed by noise (one of the reasons to select Tower Deluxe besides the private elevator and custom bath)The room rate, even with the upgrade, was, we thought, good value for money. The hotel is very nicely located (visited two other hotels we'd considered: the Venetian across the street, not impressed, and the Bellagio down the street .. quite impressed)We went to three restaurants; the Onda was fantastic, but only open the first of the three days. Japonais was so -so, but the California Pizza Kitchen and the poolside cafe was better than we expected. The pool bar was quite enjoyable, with better than average frozen drinks. Unfortunately on our last day there was a strong thunderstorm and all guests had to vacate the pool and bar .. pretty unusual for Las Vegas. The best part of our stay was the Cirque de Soleil &quot;Love&quot; .. got 3rd row tickets and it was worth it .. one of the best performances we've seen, and though the crowds in line looked formidable, all went smoothly.My favorable rating was, I'll admit, influenced by coming out a little ahead at blackjack. However, we were disappointed (not being LV regulars and coming from a fairly formal southern city) in the hordes of overweight t-shirted people coming and going throughout the ground floor. We were way overdressed (except for the Bellagio, which we visited and may return to)	
