Jul 19 2009 	Great value comfort amenities and location right on the Strip	Stayed for 5 nights with my extended family. We all loved the hotel. The rooms were comfortable size, the beds were amazingly comfortable. I was even more comfortable at the hotel, than on my Tempurpedic mattress at home. Nice modern furnishings and decor. Flat screen tv on the wall. No coffee or refrigerator in the basic room (does have minibar in rooms). The location makes it easy to walk over to Caesars, Venetian,the Palazzo, and (tram to)Treasure Island. The pool area was a beautiful oasis with lagoon styling, cooling waterfall, and lots of chairs. We did not go to the topless pool area. The restaurants were good, we enjoyed breakfast at the Paradise Cafe near the pool. The Cravings Buffet was great, go for the prime rib and crab legs; they had a great selection of everything, except the desserts. There were so many places to eat, both average priced and expensive, we never had to leave the hotel to find good food. The Dolphin and Garden Exhibit was pretty good, not great. The casino was great for gambling. Tables as low at $5-10 blackjack and craps, very clean, not too smoke filled, good cocktail service. I was able to buy all my souvenirs at a good price at the hotel gift store. I loved the spa, I just used it to work-out, sit in the hot tub, and shower, but I felt very comfortable there.I would highly recommend staying at the Mirage on your next trip to Vegas.	
Jul 18 2009 	Nice Stay	My colleague and I stayed at the Mirage in mid-July while we were in Vegas for a conference. The pool view room we requested was not available when we checked in at 12:30am, so they gave us a small credit and we moved to a pool view room the next day. Both rooms were decorated nicely and the beds are unbelievably comfortable. I went right to sleep each night! The room was clean every day when we returned from our conference and the staff we encountered throughout our stay was polite and professional. A big thanks to Vincent at the Concierge desk who helped us with our tickets to see Mystere at TI. He was so patient! We attempted to go the fitness center, but there is a charge of $25 per day to use it (I guess you can use the spa also). We opted to walk down the Strip. Can you believe it's not very busy at 7:00am?We ate at Cravings, BLT Burger, and had coffee at the Roasted Bean and Starbucks. The prices are high at each eatery, but I think that's just Las Vegas. Food and drinks were good. We also ate at the dinner buffet at Treasure Island, Wasuzu at Encore, Bon Ami at Paris, and coffee spots at Caesars and the Venetian. We had tasty meals at all the restaurants mentioned. Since we were there for a conference, we did not have much time to gamble, so I cannot comment on the casino. The pool was beautiful! We didn't visit the pool until around 5 or so each day, so we didn't have to fight for a chair. I liked that this pool offers bits of shade since it's still hot (95 degrees at 5) in the late afternoon. Will be back some day!	
