ocation and the pool and the newly rennovated room are really nice, stay here if its your first time to vegas as although its a large hotel its not overwhelming like some and the location means it is easy to get everywhere. there are quite a few restaurants in the hotel, we ate at carneige deli the first night as we were so tired we didnt want to be walking around trying to find somewhere to eat the portions are so huge though you really should share. we also ate at california pizza kitchen as there was always a long queue we figured it would be good. it was ok our waiter wasnt great. i really enjoyed my stay here and would certaintly stay again!	
