Jun 24 2009 	Love the Mirage	My husband and I got married in Las Vegas back in October and decided to stay at The Mirage-- I am really glad we did. The Mirage isn't really a 'themed' hotel which is nice, and it is def. an upscale but affordable hotel. I feel like this hotel is great if you want something nice but can't afford the more expensive ones like Bellagio, Wynn, or Venetian.Everything was nice and clean, upscale, along with a nice lobby with a giant aquarium behind check in. There is a zoo and a dolphin habitat which we went to and saw a baby dolphin--so cute! Rooms are average size and remodeled and clean. Everything looks new and fresh with a modern twist.Also the location is wonderful--strip access is good, you just walk down 1/2 block to get to the street and then you are right across from The Venetian, next to Ceasars and Treasure Island. If you want to eat cheap there is a Mcdonalds, Panda Express and Chipote across the street.	
