Jun 22 2009 	Perfect stay for first time in Vegas	My now husband and I travelled to Las Vegas to get married in May 2009. I had read a number of reviews on trip advisor and had some concerns about staying at the Mirage but I need not have worried as it was fabulous! We arrived to be greeted by a lovely man who took our bags for us and said to call when we were in our rooms and our luggage would be delivered. I was a little apprehensive leaving our luggage with him as my wedding dress was in one of the cases and we joked with him about this, he assured me not to worry. On entering the hotel I was in awe of the beauty of the lobby and for finally arriving here. Check in was smooth and no longer than I would have expected as we had a few rooms to get sorted as family and friends were with us. My husband and I were staying in one of the suites and it was amazing. Just fabulous. We called for our luggage and it was brought up within about 10 mins, no problems at all. Also asked for some extra hangers and they were brought up promptly too. Everything in the room was in good working order and we had no complaints. Housekeeping were excellent and I never saw them which to be honest is how I think it should be. The room was cleaned every day and even on the days when we didnt maybe leave the room till before lunchtime. All the restaurants that we sampled were lovely and we tried most of them. The buffet is a little expensive at the weekend but there is alot of food and a good selection but Im not sure we ate enough to get our moneys worth, if you have a big appetite its definately worth it. The majority of staff we encountered were friendly and we enjoyed gambling in the casino as most of the croupiers were a laugh. Drinks could be slow at times which was a little annoying but I noticed it seemed to be like this more during the day. We didnt win big but think thats fair to say of all casinos really. The pool was lovely, although the waterfall wasnt working during our stay and we were there for 12 days but it really is a nice area to sunbathe and soak up the sun. We ordered room service on our wedding day and it was a little pricey but was delivered on time and the food was excellent. We ordered it the night before to ensure we got it when we wanted. My only complaint about our stay at the Mirage was the elevators. Only 3 were working the majority of our stay so we had to wait a while sometimes to get up to our room but to be honest it didnt ruin the holiday and it was only a minor hassle when coming and going but you are out and about that much anyway. We went to see the beatles Love show and I would highly recommend it. Was amazing and the theatre is set up so that even if you dont buy an expensive seat you will still get a good view which was good! Really just amazing though, definate must see! The wee tram to TI is great too and we used it alot as the restaurants in there were good too. The volcano is a must see too and is really impressive...the heat that comes from it is intense and adds to the moment!! Would highly recommend the Mirage as its location on the strip is perfect and it really is a lovely hotel. Despite all the other hotels we visited I still felt the Mirage had something and it really is a great place to stay.	
