Jun 18 2009 	Mirage - Good-bye to a once great hotel	Arrival - My wife and I just came back from our Las Vegas trip 06/12-06/15 and we stayed in the Penthouse Suite at the Mirage hotel. My wife and I always stayed at the Mirage hotel since we had VIP status at the hotel and always received excellent service. I wish that was true for this trip. I booked the Penthouse Suite a month in advance and requested a volcano view. When we arrived at the hotel, we noticed that there were no people checking into the hotel which is not a good sign. In all the years I've been to the Mirage, I had never seen the lobby empty at the Mirage. I went to the Guest Check-in window and the gentleman checking us in gave us a room in the back of the hotel overlooking the highway. I politely asked for the front of the hotel and he acted like he could care less and said there were no Penthouse Suites available in the front. He suggested that I check back in a day or two. What? I said never mind and took the Penthouse Suite E-50. Elevators - Still working on the elevators but they are working.Room - Penthouse Suites are nice but very old and worn. We had light bulbs burned out in the entertainment center and we were missing complimentary robes and slippers. I know this sounds petty but this neglect did not happen when Steve Wynn owned the hotel. I would also like to mention that the entire weekend we were on our floor we only saw 1 couple on the floor. The entire E floor was silent day and night and it felt like we had the entire floor to ourselves. Kind of amazing since the check-in clerk told us that all the Penthouse Suites in the front were taken. I would have expected to hear or see some people on the E floor. Hmmmm!Craving Buffet - I think the name implies to crave a buffet somewhere else. My wife and I never had a buffet this bad in all the years we ate in Las Vegas. The selection of food was very limited and the food was terrible. They also had the wrong signage at the stations so you had no idea what your were looking at. The only good item we liked was the Gelato ice cream for dessert. Yummy! They had the nerve to charge $25.00 per person for this awful food. Never again!Slot Machines - Did they turn Las Vegas into a penny and nickel arcade? I could not believe all of the penny and nickel slot machines on the floor. All of the slot machines we played (.01, .05, .25, $1.00) were tight. Are the casinos trying to keep gamblers away? Why play a penny machine with 300 credits when you can play the dollar machine and receive a better payout?Show (Terry Fator) - I have to admit that Terry Fator is awesome and put on an excellent show. I was a little hesitant to pay the high ticket prices for a guy with puppets but he does have a live 7 piece band on stage as part of his show. We sat in row GG seats 5 &amp; 6 which is the 7th row center of stage. Excellent seats! In my opinion, Terry Fator is worth the ticket price because he is a ventriloquist, comedian, and impressionist and he puts on a great show.Check-out - We checked out of the Mirage hotel and the lady asked me how was my stay at the hotel. I informed her of the issues and she definitely agreed on the Craving Buffet She said the original buffet was excellent and she hears a lot of complaints on the new buffet and I agreed. As for my other issues, she acted like she could care less. Conclusion - My wife and I decided that this was our last time we will stay at the Mirage. The Mirage used to have excellent service and always did their best to please their guests but now the employees morale is very low and the neglect is showing at the hotel. Our future stays will be either at Wynn/Encore, Venetian, and Palazzo hotels.	
