Jun 15 2009 	Do Not Fear the Mirage	We stayed at the Mirage from Monday June 8th until Thursday June 11th, 2009. I had been monitoring Tripadvisor for weeks prior to our visit and was a little concerned about staying there as some reviewers were unkind, to say the least. However, we found the hotel to be very nice. We arrived at 11am and walked right up to the check in counter. There was no one else checking in. We could have gotten into a room right then but opted to wait for a room on a higher floor with at view of the Strip. We were told the room might not be set until 3pm but when we checked back after lunch at 12:30pm it was ready. The location is great. All the rooms (except the suites) are remodeled. The bathrooms are small but no smaller then your average hotel room. A $5 daily tip to the housekeeping staff insured plenty of clean towels, toiletries, and prompt daily cleanings. The hotel is dated (it is 20 years old) but very clean. The pools are cold however it is usually around 100 degrees in Vegas so cold is good. The waterfalls were working. That 'sour' smell of the pool others have noted is not a sour smell, it is salt. The mirage pools are saltwater based. As far as 'debries' in the pool it is worth noteing that the pool area is very tropical. There are lots of palm and other trees, some of which were flowering and dropping little yellow flowers on the pool deck. I would not count flowers as debries. The staff was friendly and helpful. Drinks are expensive at the pool but they are large. I do not consider $18 to $22 for a 32 oz alcoholic drink (and you keep the glass) a bad deal. You only really need one. Get to the pool early (before 10am) if you want a good seat. Anytime of day there were seats available they just may not be easy to find.The Stack restaurant is very good. Ask for the prix fixe menu. At $29 per person it is a great deal and the food was excellent. BLT Burger is also good. The Combo included a burger, fries, and a milkshake for $19 and the portions were just right. All and all I would recommend the Mirage and would stay there again.	
