Jun 13 2009 	It was good enough	Stayed at the Mirage from Sunday 07jun09-Thursday 11jun09. There were 3 women in the room and we never felt cramped. Check in was fast as there were only a couple of people in line. It’s a little disorienting when you arrive and have to walk your luggage through the casino. Next time I visit I will be prepared for this. A casino is hard enough to navigate without your luggage. We did arrive at 2300 though so it's prime casino time. Our room was the 2nd to last room in one of the hallways. It took like 3 solid minutes of walking to get there. I took a photo from the start of the hall and had one of the girls stand at our door and you can’t see her in the picture lol We didn’t have to worry about the calories too much with all of the walking. The room was clean and a fair size. The bathroom I didn’t find too small, just that the door is too close to the toilet. The mini fridge will charge you for anything if you take it out even if it’s just to look at it. They have sensors in them. The hotel is very pretty on the outside. There is so much foliage that it’s kind of a tropical setting in a concrete jungle (pls excuse the cliché but it’s true :) If we hadn't already unpacked I would have asked to switch to a closer room. The maids come early so put your sign out if you don't want to be woken before 0900. They knock on the door and if you don't answer, they come in. If they see you sleeping they will say sorry and leave. They did a good job everyday.At night you had to show your card to get into the elevator section which was nice for security.We ate at the Mirage buffet for lunch – they had a great salad bar where an attendant makes and mixes your salad – it was so good, they had an Asian part which wasn’t so good – it was North American fast food, A sushi section I didn’t try, Some bad Mexican, some bad Italian, a middle eastern section, Fresh Prime Rib and fixings, picnic salads, cracked crab legs and shrimp, plus dessert with a Gelato Bar. We also had dinner here and it was mostly the same. Again, had a great salad! There was always something to choose but it wasn’t very good. The only bad part was when some pitas at the Middle Eastern section were moldy. I informed a staff member from the kitchen and he picked out the pieces rather than take the whole basket away. Lunch was just under $20pp and dinner was just under $30 pp without tipBLT Burger. It was so good. The portions are huge and neither of us finished anything. I would recommend spending the extra $3.00 and splitting it. I got a burger with blue cheese and sautéed onions with lattice fries and a lunch box milkshake (vanilla ice-cream, peanut butter and grape jelly – a little sweet, but so good!). My friend got a burger with cheese and bacon, onion rings and a Nut Job milkshake (it tasted like a Ferrero Rocher). We drank a ¼ of the milkshake, most of the burger without the bun and about 3 onion rings and 3 fries each. We were so full. We could have split it and been satisfied. The combos are about $21 pp plus $1.50 for added toppings. The Milkshakes took a little while to come out because they take a while to make, but the food was fast. Our bill was $46 for 2 without tip.Chipotle's, Chinese and McDonald's are right across the street and in O'Shea's across the street are Burger King, some pizza place and Subway for cheap eats.The Mirage Casino: We spent most nights at the Mirage. Drink service is pretty good there. There were only a couple of times through the stay where we waited for a while. Mostly they were awesome. The casino is also really easy to navigate after 1 night and we had a lot of fun during our visit. The Revolution Lounge is pretty cool looking but we didn’t go there to drink because we were 10 feet away drinking for free while we gambled. Stupidly we also didn’t learn till our last night that there is a club through the doorway in Revolution lounge. We thought it was only a lounge. Had we have learned this earlier we would have gone in. We also didn’t go to Jet or RumBar. I would have liked to visit a couple night clubs but the other girls didn’t show any interest. They went to stay at the pool all day and gamble all night.Mirage Pool: The girls with the kids were so excited to relax at the pool without hearing “Mom” every minute. This is the first time that either has spent more than a night away from their children. They went to the pool every morning for hours. They would wake up at 0800 and sit there till 1300. I went the first day for 2 hours and didn’t go back. I love pools but I’ve never been to Vegas and I wanted to spend as much time as I could exploring. Next time I’m in Vegas I will spend more time at the pool because you have all night to walk around. None of us liked the pool. It’s large and pretty but they cram you in there! The chairs were touching on both sides. You couldn’t fit anything between them and there were 10-15 chairs in a row. The only place to move the chairs would be into an aisle which would interrupt everyone else. I mentioned in another post that prisons would offer more room between their chairs. You had to show a room key everyday and they always had fresh towels and were very friendly. The cocktail waitresses made their rounds often. The two girls ordered Miami Vice’s one day. The waitress said they come with about 5 shots each in a keepsake glass for $18 each. Vegas cocktail prices at the pool. They only had the one but said it was super yummy. We didn’t go into Bare so can’t review it. The pool area had people of all shapes, sizes and ages. There weren't a lot of children there.The Mirage has a game by the buffet called “Native Spirit”. It has a tower with bonuses and makes loon and other animal noises. It was pretty fun and I won some money on my last night and then my last day. I won about $80 each time. Most likely what I had previously lost! I only mostly played penny slots but full lines and sometimes multiplied. So it can add up to $1.80 a pull. Overall I am glad I stayed at the Mirage. I liked the size of the property, the rooms, the bed, the casino, BLT Burger and the location. I didn't care for the pool or find the staff very friendly. Again, they weren't rude, just not welcoming. I would stay again for a good price but go somewhere else if I could. I'd like to try Planet Hollywood because I liked the Vibe. It would be a good hotel for people 21-40 without kids.I did have a problem with my room key not working. It would take 6-12 times before it worked. I got the card replaced and it still did it. The other girls tried my card and had the same problem but their cards were fine. Don't give up after 3 tried and go all the way to the front desk; I would try about 15 times first.	
