May 24 2009 	WOW! Great hotel love the pool... but I don't like the location	My husband and I usually stay at the Monte Carlo, however, we decided to try out this hotel (there was a really good package deal) last Aug. The experience at this hotel was awesome! The staff is super nice and accommodating - much better than the Monte Carlo which is a 3-star hotel. I didn't think it would make much difference but the Mirage staff treated us much better, they really wanted us to enjoy our stay. The hotel room was nice and clean. I think it was pretty standard. The cleaning service was great. They were efficient and very good. The casino was good but I don't think we played a lot there. There are many high end restaurants there but we didn't try them out (too much $$$ for us). We ate at California Pizza Kitchen (it's was pretty good) and Carnegie Deli - also pretty good. We loved their pool!! The pool area is sunny with some shady areas. They have a salt water pool, no chemical which was different but very nice. The main pool was huge and even with a lot people, there was room to swim around. We were there in August so it was the hottest time of the year and everyone was in the pool but it really didn't feel overcrowded. It's sad to read in the 2009 reviews by people on this site that the waterfall was not working. It is a nice feature, it makes the scenery much more tropical. I hope they bring it back. They also have a pool for adults in a secluded area but it was overcrowded and there are too many &quot;excited&quot; boys for my taste. The hotel has a gym (yes, we do work out during our vacation!!!) - it does have all the standard cardio machines, weight machines, and free weights. It was pretty expensive because you have to buy the spa deal to get into the gym (Sorry I don't remember exact amount). The location of the hotel is right in the middle of the strip. You can walk to all the 5 star hotels. However, there is no drugstore close by (you have to walk a good distance to get to one). We don't rent a car. The hotel does sell basic stuff but they double or triple the price so it can add up. Overall, it was one of the best experiences we've had in Vegas but we really didn't like the location and we ended up paying more than usual for many things.	
