May 21 2009 	Great first stay at the Mirage	We stayed at the Mirage May 8-11, 2009, and visited Vegas for a concert. We made our reservations back in January and got a great deal....lowest prices I've seen for this resort in the last few years, the price even went down further online and I called and got it adjusted through their reservations department. So watch the websites after you book, they will always meet the internet price if it goes down. Great deal! Took a taxi to the hotel from the airport and were greeted on arrival by a friendly valet. We went to the front desk to see if our rooms were ready even though it was early, around noon. We asked to be put on the same floor as another couple we were traveling with. The front desk person was nice and easily accommodated our request and had 2 rooms ready for us right away on the 9th floor. I would've liked to ask for room on a higher floor, but knowing about the elevator issues, I did not. (Glad we stayed with low floors, I saw lines for the upper floor elevators every day at almost all times of the day or night.) Our elevator area had already been renovated so we encountered no issues there. The room was nice and newly renovated. Flat panel tv, cool design, etc. Very nice. The dark carpet does show every speck of lint and dust though. Could've used a thorough vacuuming but it was not bad. Everything else looked very clean. We had a strip view and could see Treasure Island, Wynn, Venetian, etc. No issues with housekeeping at all. I liked how they had a lot of towels in the room too. I counted 6 on arrival and 4 at the lowest amount. Nice! No need to ask for extra towels at all.We ate at BLT Burger the first day for lunch. Food was a bit on the high side, but very good overall. Neat place to grab something. I had the Kobe slider trio and my friend tried one of the spiked milkshakes which was delicious!! I also got carryout late one night to take back to the room. Service was prompt even then.We also ate at the Caribe Cafe our first morning for breakfast. Service was very quick and the food was good. Prices were ok....not too low, not too high. Faster service than other cafes I've been to at other casino hotels in Vegas though.Played some slots here, but found that they did not have some of the newer slots like Wizard of Oz, Star Trek or Quarter Wheel of Fortune we were looking for. Mostly played Goldfish or video poker. Table minimums were too high for me here, but I did see $10 blackjack tables during the day. Played $3 blackjack downtown and had better luck on slots downtown also. The pool....same deal here as anyplace else. You gotta play the save a pool chair game. It is annoying but it happens everywhere else (Flamingo, Mandalay) so what can you do. We did not get down there very early, maybe around 9ish and we were able to eventually get enough chairs. People start to leave later in the day so chairs free up more then. There are pool attendants that will help you find chairs if needed. The pool area is really nice, pretty landscaping, lots of palm trees, both shade or sun available. The pool bar was convenient but somewhat high priced. $20 for a daquiri. Keeps you from drinking too much I guess. The last day I asked for a late checkout and they gave me an extra hour, till 1pm at no charge. I forget what the cost was for extra time. I checked my bag with the bellhops until it was time to leave for the airport. Friendly bellhops as well, even though they were quite busy. Overall, all of the Mirage employees I encountered to be very helpful and friendly. Ate at 777 Brew Pub at Main Street Station the first night. Great value. Been there twice now and loved it again. Plan to return. Also ate at Mon Ami Gabi at Paris one night and got a table on the patio! yay! Got to see the fountains. I had called ahead for a reservation, but I'm not sure it was needed. It was early and not busy when we arrived. There was a line when we left though. Ate at Wynn Buffet for mother's day brunch...that was amazing and fabulous. Moms got a rose and small bag of candy. Huge variety of food! I've been to the buffet at Bellagio several times before and we liked this buffet better. The dining room is nicer the way it has natural light and smaller rooms. Food quality and selection is comparable to the Bellagio though. Also tried Diablo’s at Monte Carlo one night. It was just ok. Not the greatest Mexican food, not the worst. Overall, an awesome trip to Vegas! I would book the Mirage again. Great amenities, pool and location. Can’t wait to go back in the fall!	
