May 19 2009 	Ok if you like staying in a railway station!!	To be fair I will write both the good and bad and hope that this will help someone trying to decide to stay there. The good. The location is great in the midst of the big casinos. Casaers Palace and Treasure Island are next door. Across the road is Harrahs, Wynn, Venetian etc. You would not need a car if you want to casino hop. The pool is very attractive with maybe 75 palm trees and an interesting shape and layout that can provide shade and a feeling that there is not that many people. Parking access is not bad once you get used to the confusing signs pointing to the self park. Acceess is between Mirage and TI off the strip. The walk to the hotel is not bad. The bad. The rooms were semi renovated. I say semi because they were redecorated but really redone. Example the night table and dresser had a glass top added over the old furniture to make it look new. The tub had been resurfaced not replaced. In one large spot the paint had split and rust was pouring through indicating that they would soon need to redo. The original beds had a mattress topper added and were slightly more comfortable. The TV had been replaced with a flat screen. Room attendent missed something wveryday. The wine glasses were removed. She told us they were removing them from all the rooms and to call room service to get more. One day there were no face cloths. The next day there were no hand towels. She said she was not given any clean towels. One day the safe decided to not work. We had to wait one hour to get them to open for us. THis also happened when we first arrived and also lost one hour waiting. The walk from the front desk to the elevators is a windy path through the casino. This is very very crowded all the time and very narrow. It is a real pain with your luggage. The machines in the casino are extremely tight. I would avoid them. I played the poker room but got no points credit becasue their computer was down. The next day the poker room manager refused to credit my play. VERY VERY POOR ATTITUDE. We decided to play in other casnios. We were staying one week and wanted a good gambling experience. Avoid the buffet at all costs. The greeter was very rude. The food was mediocre at best considering the price. I suggest you cross the street and go the Wynn, Venetian or the Paris for MUCH better food and service. The pool was very crowded. People grab the chairs at 8:00 and leave towels on them to hog them for the day. So by 8:30 most of the chairs are taken but hardly any people in the pool. We found it was not bad to go around 5:00 and swim until 7:00 closing. The other thing is play the same hogging game everyone else does. The pool waterfall was not working and the whole area around that was ropped off. I would not stay here again considering all the better choices out there. My wife and I go 3 times a year and have stayed in most of them.	
